description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This role represents an exciting opportunity to join the newly created &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Ambulatory Care &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Division in a critical role working closely with the Divisional Leadership Team. This individual will work in a unique role in the Division&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; leading on strategy development and the financial efficiency and sustainability of the Division. The role will be a key link for specialty and directorate colleagues&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; providing both leadership of Divisional level or multi-specialty projects including the delivery of the Division wide activity and capacity plan. The individual will work closely with the Divisional General Manager on oversight of and support to the new Directorate structure. The individual will have the opportunity to work &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;across &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;both Divisional and organisation&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;al&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; boundaries &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;on areas &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;aligned to our strategic development. The individual will be a source of experience and advice to guide Directorates efficiently through the Trust governance processes&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; supporting effective business case development and ensuring alignment with both the Division and Trusts strategic intent. You will be a good communicator, able to create wide and effective working relationships and be able to engage and lead teams towards a clear vision.’&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NamePaul SillandyJob titleDivisional General Manager - Ambulatory CareEmail addressPaul.Sillandy@nuh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
